.SH SYNOPSIS
.sp
pychroot [\-h] [\-\-version] [\-\-hostname HOSTNAME] [\-\-skip\-chdir] [\-B SRC[:DEST]] [\-R SRC[:DEST]] [\-\-ro SRC[:DEST]] path ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
pychroot is an extended \fBchroot(1)\fP equivalent that also provides support for
automatically handling bind mounts.
.SH POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B path
path to newroot
.TP
.B command
optional command to run
.UNINDENT
.SH OPTIONAL ARGUMENTS
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-h\fP,\fB  \-\-help
show this help message and exit
.TP
.B \-\-version
show program\(aqs version number and exit
.TP
.BI \-\-hostname \ HOSTNAME
specify the chroot hostname
.TP
.B \-\-skip\-chdir
do not change working directory to \(aq/\(aq
.UNINDENT
.sp
\-B SRC[:DEST], \-\-bind SRC[:DEST]        specify custom bind mount
.sp
\-R SRC[:DEST], \-\-rbind SRC[:DEST]       specify custom recursive bind mount
.sp
\-\-ro SRC[:DEST], \-\-readonly SRC[:DEST]  specify custom readonly bind mount
